{
  "stem": "17426.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 96.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And oftentimes, at each station that we came, we had to get rid of these-- those that had died.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the SS just said to us, just toss them over the wagon, just toss them over the edge of the train.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so whoever wasn't completely dead was also dead by the time he landed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 13 SECONDS] Many of the inmates lost their minds and were shot.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And when civilians were trying to bring us some water some time at the station, they were being driven away by the SS.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And oftentimes we passed passenger cars with dining rooms and looked at their lives and thought how different one who is not born a Jew, who is born a German, can live, even during the war.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was such a discrepancy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was such a hard thing to realize, that misery was only for us, not for everyone.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And so [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] as the rails were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] free, we were brought closer and closer to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And with each joint of the rail, I'd lay there and hear the voice-- doom, death, doom, death, doom, death, doom, death.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I thought I'd lose my mind.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I looked at my brothers in the wagon, my father, and said to myself, don't they know?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is doom.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is death.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I know, the rails told me that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so on the fifth day-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] dirty, unwashed, hungry, depleted of strength-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] our wagons stopped.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And it was dawn.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We looked outside, and we saw [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] that where-- we are at a camp.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
